OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FTax self-assessment: HMRC  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwaives fines again for late
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffilings                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Fines will be waived for anyone who    
OL,6, submits their self-assessment tax      
OL,7, return up to a month after the normal  
OL,8, deadline of 31 January.                
OL,10,FHM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) said     
OL,11,Ffines would not be enforced for anyone 
OL,12,Fwho files by 28 February.              
OL,14,FThe move has been met with surprise.   
OL,15,FTypically, not meeting the deadline    
OL,16,Fresults in an automatic #100 penalty.  
OL,18,FHMRC said Covid had put added pressure 
OL,19,Fon individuals and tax advisers to     
OL,20,Fcomplete online submissions.           
